'''Sarah Doron''' ({{lang-he|<U+05E9><U+05E8><U+05D4> <U+05D3><U+05D5><U+05E8><U+05D5><U+05DF>}}, 20 May 1922 &ndash; 2 November 2010) was a former [[Israel]]i politician who served as a [[Minister without Portfolio]] from July 1983 until September 1984.

==Biography==
Born in [[Kaunas]] in [[Lithuania]], Doron made [[aliyah]] to [[British Mandate of Palestine|Mandate Palestine]] in 1933. She attended high school in [[Tel Aviv]], and was later elected to the city's council, where she chaired the municipal education committee.

A chairwoman of Liberal Women's Organization, she was elected to the [[Knesset]] in 1977 on [[Likud]]'s list. Re-elected in 1981, she was appointed Minister without Portfolio by [[Menachem Begin]] on 5 July 1983. She remained a [[cabinet of Israel|cabinet]] member when [[Yitzhak Shamir]] formed a new government in October 1983.

Although Doron retained her seat in the [[Israeli legislative election, 1984|1984 elections]], she was left out of the [[national unity government]] cabinet. She was re-elected again in 1988, but lost her seat in the [[Israeli legislative election, 1992|1992 elections]].

Doron died on 2 November 2010 at the age of 88.

